  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you add a profile picture on Quora?",
  "response": "To add or change your profile picture on Quora, follow these steps:\n\n### **On Desktop:**\n1. **Log In**: Sign in to your Quora account.\n2. **Go to Your Profile**: Click on your current profile picture or your name at the top right corner of the screen, then select \"Profile\" from the dropdown menu.\n3. **Edit Profile**: Click the \"Edit Profile\" button (it looks like a pencil icon) on your profile page.\n4. **Change Picture**: Hover over your current profile picture and click the camera icon that appears.\n5. **Upload a Photo**: Choose a photo from your computer and adjust it as needed.\n6. **Save Changes**: Click \"Save\" to update your profile picture.\n\n### **On Mobile (iOS/Android):**\n1. **Log In**: Open the Quora app and log in to your account.\n2. **Go to Your Profile**: Tap your profile picture or the \"More\" icon (three horizontal lines) in the bottom right corner, then select \"Profile.\"\n3. **Edit Profile**: Tap the \"Edit Profile\" button (it looks like a pencil icon).\n4. **Change Picture**: Tap your current profile picture.\n5. **Upload a Photo**: Choose a photo from your device\u2019s gallery or take a new one.\n6. **Save Changes**: Tap \"Save\" to update your profile picture.\n\n### **Tips:**\n- Make sure the image is clear and recognizable.\n- Quora recommends using a square image for best results.\n- The maximum file size for a profile picture is **5 MB**.\n\nOnce you\u2019ve updated your profile picture, it will appear next to your name on your posts, answers, and comments.",
